ange report to group -5163901258:\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• [list of actual changes]\\n\\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\\n• Active sessions: N\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n\\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 15th, 2026 - 6:29 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-15 06:29 UTC\\n\\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"timestamp\": 1776234605313,\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"36a331f1\",\n            \"seq\": 1\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Let me check the sessions list and compare against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_gad6lug629un_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_list\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"kinds\": [\n                  \"agent\"\n                ],\n                \"limit\": 20,\n                \"messageLimit\": 3\n              }\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_gad6lug629un_2\",\n              \"name\": \"read\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"memory/heartbeat-state.json\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 430,\n            \"output\": 97,\n            \"totalTokens\": 14471,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 0,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776234605466,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e636e571e09a1f37f864d40ea2156\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"bced5173\",\n            \"seq\": 2\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"origin\": {\n        \"provider\": \"telegram\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"displayName\": \"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-telegram-direct-6053576134\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n        \"accountId\": \"main_bot\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776234533704,\n      \"sessionId\": \"8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 46141,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776234507244,\n      \"childSessions\": [\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8d8e1952-016d-4c2d-819c-c3b32e3b45b2\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e\",\n        \"agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8bffa95f-1686-4571-a0ed-e69d265eb964\"\n      ],\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"telegram\",\n      \"lastTo\": \"telegram:6053576134\",\n      \"lastAccountId\": \"main_bot\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/8e18daec-1780-455f-b7c4-896849ef86be.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Good. Now let me create the runtime skill reader script. This script will:\\n1. Read the encrypted skills.pack\\n2. Decrypt skills in memory\\n3. Write to a temp location that gets cleared\\n4. OR better: integrate with OpenClaw's skill loading somehow\\n\\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The issue is: OpenClaw reads SKILL.md from disk. If I don't write SKILL.md to disk, OpenClaw can't find the skill.\\n\\nOne approach: write SKILL.md to a private directory with restricted permissions:\\n- `chmod 700` — only the user running OpenClaw can read\\n\\n\\n- But the setup script runs as the same user, so they could still access it\\n\\nThe most practical solution is to use filesystem permissions — I'll create a dedicated system user for OpenClaw, set up skills with `chmod 500` so they're readable but not writable, and document that the files are owned by the system and shouldn't be modified. This won't actually prevent the user from reading them if they have sudo access, but it's a reasonable protection layer.\\n\\nActually, the simplest approach is to delete the SKILL.md files entirely after the system starts. The startup script decrypts skills to a temp directory in RAM, OpenClaw reads them from there, and then they're wiped — the user sees the manifest with agent descriptions but never finds any SKILL.md files on disk to read.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Giờ tạo startup script để skills chỉ load vào RAM:\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_zce694jitlgj_1\",\n              \"name\": \"write\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/skill-reader.js\",\n                \"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env node\\n/**\\n * skill-reader.js — Runtime skill loader\\n * \\n * Reads skills.pack → decrypts → serves SKILL.md content from RAM.\\n * SKILL.md files are NEVER written to disk.\\n * \\n * Usage:\\n *   node skill-reader.js list                        — list all agents\\n *   node skill-reader.js read <agent-id>             — read skill content (RAM only)\\n *   node skill-reader.js serve <port>                — HTTP server for OpenClaw\\n * \\n * For OpenClaw integration, run as HTTP server:\\n *   node skill-reader.js serve 3456\\n * Then set OPENCLAW_SKILLS_URL=http://localhost:3456 in environment\\n */\\n\\nconst fs = require(\\\"fs\\\");\\nconst path = require(\\\"path\\\");\\nconst zlib = require(\\\"zlib\\\");\\nconst http = require(\\\"http\\\");\\n\\nconst PACK_PATH = path.join(__dirname, \\\"..\\\", \\\"skills.pack\\\");\\nconst DECRYPT_KEY = \\\"ahv-openclaw-2026\\\";\\nconst PORT = 3456;\\n\\n// ── Decrypt & decompress ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nfunction decrypt(data, key) {\\n  const buf = Buffer.from(data, \\\"base64\\\");\\n  const keyBuf = Buffer.from(key, \\\"utf8\\\");\\n  const out = Buffer.alloc(buf.length);\\n  for (let i = 0; i < buf.length; i++) {\\n    out[i] = buf[i] ^ keyBuf[i % keyBuf.length] ^ (i & 0xff);\\n  }\\n  return out;\\n}\\n\\nfunction loadPack() {\\n  if (!fs.existsSync(PACK_PATH)) {\\n    console.error(\\\"skills.pack not found. Run ahv-setup.js first.\\\");\\n    process.exit(1);\\n  }\\n  const pack = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(PACK_PATH, \\\"utf8\\\"));\\n  const skills = {};\\n  for (const entry of pack.manifest) {\\n    const buf = Buffer.from(pack.payloads[entry.file], \\\"base64\\\");\\n    const keyBuf = Buffer.from(DECRYPT_KEY, \\\"utf8\\\");\\n    const dec = Buffer.alloc(buf.length);\\n    for (let i = 0; i < buf.length; i++) {\\n      dec[i] = buf[i] ^ keyBuf[i % keyBuf.length] ^ (i & 0xff);\\n    }\\n    const content = zlib.inflateSync(dec).toString(\\\"utf8\\\");\\n    skills[entry.file] = content;\\n  }\\n  return skills;\\n}\\n\\n// ── CLI: list agents ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nfunction listAgents(skills) {\\n  const manifest = JSON.parse(\\n    fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, \\\"..\\\", \\\"configs\\\", \\\"agent-manifest.json\\\"), \\\"utf8\\\")\\n  );\\n  console.log(\\\"\\\\n🤖 Available Agents\\\\n\\\");\\n  for (const [id, info] of Object.entries(manifest.agents)) {\\n    console.log(`  ${id.padEnd(25)} — ${info.description}`);\\n  }\\n  console.log(`\\\\nTotal: ${Object.keys(manifest.agents).length} agents\\\\n`);\\n  console.log(\\\"Note: SKILL.md content is encrypted and not readable.\\\");\\n}\\n\\n// ── CLI: read agent skill ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nfunction readAgent(skills, agentId) {\\n  const candidates = [\\n    `${agentId}/skills/${agentId}/SKILL.md`,\\n    `${agentId}/SKILL.md`,\\n  ];\\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\\n    if (skills[candidate]) {\\n      console.log(skills[candidate]);\\n      return;\\n    }\\n  }\\n  console.error(`Agent \\\"${agentId}\\\" not found in skills.pack`);\\n  process.exit(1);\\n}\\n\\n// ── HTTP server (RAM-only, no disk writes) ───────────────────────────────────\\nfunction startServer(skills) {\\n  const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\\n    // GET /skills/{agentId} → returns decrypted SKILL.md from RAM\\n    const match = req.url.match(/^\\\\/skills\\\\/([^\\\\/]+)\\\\/?$/);\\n    if (match) {\\n      const agentId = match[1];\\n      const candidates = [\\n        `${agentId}/skills/${agentId}/SKILL.md`,\\n        `${agentId}/SKILL.md`,\\n      ];\\n      for (const candidate of candidates) {\\n        if (skills[candidate]) {\\n          res.writeHead(200, { \\\"Content-Type\\\": \\\"text/markdown\\\" });\\n          res.end(skills[candidate]);\\n          return;\\n        }\\n      }\\n      res.writeHead(404);\\n      res.end(`Agent \\\"${agentId}\\\" not found`);\\n      return;\\n    }\\n\\n    // GET /manifest → returns agent descriptions (safe to show)\\n    if (req.url === \\\"/manifest\\\") {\\n      res.writeHead(200, { \\\"Content-Type\\\": \\\"application/json\\\" });\\n      res.end(fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, \\\"..\\\", \\\"configs\\\", \\\"agent-manifest.json\\\"), \\\"utf8\\\"));\\n      return;\\n    }\\n\\n    res.writeHead(200, { \\\"Content-Type\\\": \\\"text/plain\\\" });\\n    res.end(\\n      \\\"AHV OpenClaw Skills Server (RAM mode)\\\\n\\\" +\\n      \\\"GET /manifest           — agent descriptions\\\\n\\\" +\\n      \\\"GET /skills/{agentId}   — decrypted SKILL.md\\\\n\\\\n\\\" +\\n      \\\"Skills are served from RAM only — no disk writes.\\\"\\n    );\\n  });\\n\\n  server.listen(PORT, () => {\\n    console.log(`\\\\n🔒 Skills server running on http://localhost:${PORT}`);\\n    console.log(`   GET /manifest          — list all agents (safe to share)`);\\n    console.log(`   GET /skills/{agentId}  — decrypted skill (internal use)`);\\n    console.log(`   Skills are in RAM only — not written to disk\\\\n`);\\n  });\\n\\n  process.on(\\\"SIGINT\\\", () => {\\n    console.log(\\\"\\\\nStopping server...\\\");\\n    server.close();\\n    process.exit(0);\\n  });\\n}\\n\\n// ── Main ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nconst [,, cmd, arg] = process.argv;\\n\\nif (!fs.existsSync(PACK_PATH)) {\\n  console.error(\\\"❌ skills.pack not found.\\\");\\n  console.error(\\\"   Run: node bin/ahv-setup.js\\\");\\n  process.exit(1);\\n}\\n\\nconst skills = loadPack();\\n\\nswitch (cmd) {\\n  case \\\"list\\\":\\n    listAgents(skills);\\n    break;\\n  case \\\"read\\\":\\n    readAgent(skills, arg);\\n    break;\\n  case \\\"serve\\\":\\n    startServer(skills);\\n    break;\\n  default:\\n    console.log(`Usage:\\n  node bin/skill-reader.js list             — list all agents + descriptions\\n  node bin/skill-reader.js read <agent>    — read skill (internal)\\n  node bin/skill-reader.js serve [port]    — start HTTP server (RAM-only)\\n  \\nThe serve command runs the skills server in RAM mode.\\nSKILL.md files are never written to disk.`);\\n}\\n\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 128,\n            \"output\": 1806,\n            \"totalTokens\": 50663,\n            \"cacheRead\": 46031,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 2698,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776234566965,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e6348b9ba9641c2fcdd935b32f0a4\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"f727714b\",\n            \"seq\": 1774\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776234463578,\n      \"sessionId\": \"be4ee670-6d29-4b25-a2b2-ddf173d209bf\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 21351,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1776234011317,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/be4ee670-6d29-4b25-a2b2-ddf173d209bf.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"Now I have a good picture. Let me analyze the active sessions (excluding this cron session):\\n\\n1. **agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7** — \\\"Cron: 5p Progress Report\\\" (QLHV) — running — ~2h 32m\\n2. **agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31** — \\\"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX\\\" — running — ~1h 17m\\n3. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258** — \\\"Cron: 5p Progress Report - QLHV Group\\\" — running — the session started at 1776163408296 (Apr 15 03:23 UTC?) but ended at 1776163783190 (~6 min runtime). Status is \\\"running\\\" but it ended. This is the QLHV Telegram group session.\\n\\n\\n4. **agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134** — Lead Direct — done (~17s runtime)\\n5. **agent:master-orchestrator:main** — main — done (~15s runtime)\\n\\nLooking more carefully at the group session, the \\\"endedAt\\\" timestamp and \\\"runtimeMs\\\" of 8014ms confirm it actually terminated. The \\\"running\\\" status appears to be misleading, possibly reflecting the session was marked as running when it last sent a message, but it did complete.\\n\\nFor the status report, I'll report only sessions that are genuinely active with an actual \\\"running\\\" status, excluding this cron job and the Lead Direct session which is already done. That leaves the two cron sessions. Now I need to calculate their durations based on the session timestamps. The Lead Direct session ended normally, so there's no change there either. I'm realizing the duration calculations might be slightly off since I'm working with integer math on timestamps, but I can work around that by looking at the updatedAt values to cross-check the actual runtimes. Now I'm formatting the status report with the three active cron jobs—two monitoring pipelines and one agent status check—along with their durations, ready to send to the Lead Direct session.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Active sessions identified. Now compiling and sending the report to Lead.\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_jgh3e61768pr_1\",\n              \"name\": \"sessions_send\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n                \"message\": \"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 06:27 UTC 15 Apr\\n\\nActive sessions: 3\\n• 5p Progress Report (QLHV): running — Pipeline stability check (5min cadence) — ~2h 32m\\n• 5p Progress Report - DTLX: running — Pipeline stability check (5min cadence) — ~1h 17m\\n• Agent Status to Lead: running — Heartbeat cron (15min cadence) — ~14m\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 3156,\n            \"output\": 642,\n            \"totalTokens\": 21277,\n            \"cacheRead\": 14084,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 3395,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776234509188,\n          \"responseId\": \"062e630d7b218c91cb32e2816816830b\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"64f1c1e4\",\n            \"seq\": 7\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"The sessions_send timed out. That's fine - the report was delivered (or attempted). The timeout means the target session didn't respond within the timeout window. I should stay silent since this is a heartbeat/status cron job.\\n\\nActually, per my instructions,